{
  "text": "CREB (cAMP response-element binding protein)-BDNF (brain derived neurotrophic factor) pathway is a well known pathway in depression. A reduced BDNF mRNA level was also reported in both the prefrontal cortex and hippocampus [CITATION_1] and BDNF protein immunoreactivity was elevated in postmortem tissue from antidepressant treated patients [CITATION_2] . On the other hand, decreased hippocampal CREB was found in temporal cortex or hippocampus in depressed patients studied at autopsy [CITATION_3] and antidepressant treatment also increase CREB [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . CREB, in turn, induced several targets gene, including BDNF [CITATION_6] . Recent studies have shown that ghrelin stimulated CREB through the activation of cAMP [CITATION_7] . However, the role of CREB-BDNF pathway in antidepressant-like effect of the ghrelin was seldom reported in the ovariectomized mice.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "37248137",
